Toshiba Assigns 700 Engineers to Work on Fukushima Nuclear Plant

-- B y   M a k i   S h i r a k i
-- 
2011-03-21T05:34:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/toshiba-assigns-700-engineers-to-work-on-fukushima-nuclear-plant.html
  Toshiba Corp. (6502) , Japan’s biggest
maker of nuclear reactors, said about 700 of its engineers
have been assigned to help defuse the crisis at Tokyo Electric
Power Co.’s crippled Fukushima Dai-Ichi power plant.  The Tokyo-based company is dispatching 100 workers to the
site by today, spokesman  Keisuke Ohmori  said by telephone today.
The No. 2 reactor was supplied jointly by Toshiba and  General
Electric Co. (GE) , while Toshiba supplied the No. 3 reactor,
according to Ohmori.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maki Shiraki in Tokyo at 
